 attacks on april   pan am flight  a lockheed constellation clipper empress of the skies crashed during an attempted landing at shannon airport in ireland  flight crew and  passengers died in the crash  passenger survived with minor injuries on november   pan am flight  a boeing  stratocruiser n clipper romance of the skies disappeared over the pacific ocean en route to honolulu a week later debris and bodies were recovered the definitive cause of the accident has never been determined  passengers and crew lost their lives an accident involving a pan am plane on december   led to the faas ordering the installation of safety devices on aircraft the  named clipper tradewind npa and operating as pan am flight  was in a holding pattern on a flight from baltimore to philadelphia when it was last seen going down in flames it was determined that lightning had ignited vapors in the planes fuel tanks as a result of the disaster lightning discharge wicks were installed on all commercial airliners there were  fatalities between  and  a further five pan am s were involved in major accidents that resulted in substantial loss of lives three of these occurred on the airlines pacific network between december  and april  within a time span of five months more than  lives were lost in all five accidents twothirds of which were accounted for by the last three  fatalities september    b npa montserrat caribbean  fatalities december    b npa near caracas venezuela  fatalities july    b npa near papeete faaa  fatalities january    b npa near pago pago american samoa  fatalities april    b npa near denpasar ngurah rai bali indonesia a pan am  was also involved in an enduring cold war mystery that remains unresolved to this day which occurred on november   on that day clipper münchen a pan am boeing – npa operating the return leg of the airlines daily cargo flight from berlin to frankfurt rheinmain airport pan am flight  was due to land that night at tegel airport rather than tempelhof due to runway resurfacing work taking place at that time at the latter berlin control had cleared flight  for an instrument landing system ils approach to tegel airports runway  soon after the crew had begun its descent from flight level fl   feet to fl   feet before entering the southwest air corridor over east germany on the last stretch of its journey to berlin the aircraft impacted the ground near dallgow east germany almost immediately after the crew had acknowledged further instructions received from berlin control just  mi  km from tegel airport all three crew members lost their lives in this accident visibility was poor and it was snowing at the time of the accident following the accident the soviet military authorities in east germany returned only half of the aircrafts wreckage to their us counterparts in west berlin this excluded vital parts such as the flight data recorder fdr the cockpit voice recorder cvr as well as the planes flight control systems its navigation and communication equipment the subsequent national transportation safety board ntsb investigation report concluded that the aircrafts descent below its altitude clearance limit was the accidents probable cause however the ntsb was unable to establish the factors that had caused the crew to descend below its cleared minimum altitude on september   two men hijacked pan am flight  a boeing – npa en route from amsterdam to new york as part of the dawsons field hijackings the flight diverted to beirut international airport to take on board seven other gang members for the next leg to cairo international airport where the hijackers ordered the aircraft evacuated and destroyed it with explosives on july   pan am flight  a commercial passenger flight of a boeing  from san francisco california to saigon south vietnam was hijacked over the south china sea the lone hijacker was overpowered and killed after arrival at tan son nhut air base in saigon and no other passengers were killed or seriously injured on december   five palestinian terrorists who had taken six hostages at rome fiumicino airport bombed pan am flight  while passengers boarded the boeing b clipper celestial npa caught fire killing  people on july   clipper defiance a boeing – n operating as pan am flight  crashed minutes after takeoff from new orleans airport involving microburstinduced wind shear all  passengers and crew members perished as well as eight people on the ground when the plane careened through a residential area adjacent to the airport on august   a bomb placed under a seat cushion detonated incabin during the flight of pan am flight  a boeing – npa one passenger was killed and  injured in the explosion the flight landed safely in honolulu on november   eastern air lines captain george baines was flying in his private aircraft a piper pa np from his home to tampa international to catch a flight as he approached tampa internationals runway l now l in heavy fog he declared a missed approach and went around to try it again on the second attempt he touched down on a parallel taxiway and ultimately collided with a pan am – that was taxiing on this taxiway baines lost his life in the accident he was the only fatality no other injuries were reported pan am flight edit main article tenerife airport disaster clipper victor which was the first boeing  to carry farepaying passengers in  npa was involved in the tenerife disaster on march   the deadliest aviation accident in history on that day clipper victor operated a charter flight pa  from los angeles to las palmas in the canary islands spain via new york the aircraft along with many other aircraft diverted to los rodeos airport on tenerife because of a bomb scare at las palmas after las palmas airport reopened the diverted aircraft began preparations for departure clipper victor was instructed to taxi along the active runway after the preceding klm although visibility was extremely poor due to thick fog the pilot of the klm aircraft also a boeing  commenced takeoff without clearance and collided with the pan am airplane still taxiing on the runway a total of  people were killed  passengers on the pan am plane died while  survived pan am flight edit main article pan am flight  on september   a pan am  named the clipper empress of the seas npa operating as pan am flight  was taken over by hijackers while on a scheduled stop in karachi the flight never departed karachi but  people were killed when the aircraft was stormed on the ground the chief purser of the flight neerja bhanot an indian national was credited for saving many lives on the flight and was awarded by the indian government the us government and the pakistan government for her selfless act pan am flight edit main article pan am flight  pan am flight  was pan ams third daily scheduled transatlantic flight from london heathrow airport to new york john f kennedy airport on december   the aircraft flying this route a boeing – npa named clipper maid of the seas was blown up and crashed on lockerbie in dumfries and galloway scotland when approximately  pound  g of plastic explosive was detonated in its forward cargo hold triggering a sequence of events that led to the rapid destruction of the aircraft the aircraft that crashed was the th  built and was delivered to pan am in february  a total of  people lost their lives including  in lockerbie fleetedit fleet in edit the following were aircraft operated pan am and pan am express in march  a year and a half before the airlines collapse pan am fleet march  aircraft in service orders passengers notes f c y total airbus ab  — —    airbus a  — —    airbus a  —     boeing –   —    orders for used aircraft boeing –  — —    boeing –  —      seating configuration for south american flights boeing b  —      seating configuration total   pan am express fleet march  aircraft in service orders atr –   de havilland canada dash   — total   fleet historyedit all the aircraft ever operated by pan am pan am fleet airc